3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">1. Quality</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107483" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107483" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The most obvious difference you’ll find between cheaper ellipticals and their pricier counterparts is the quality of the materials. The standard ellipticals you’ll find in gyms are well over $1000 with many even being $2000 to $3000. With this price difference will come a large jump in the sturdiness of the build, often being able to support heavier weight and much more intensity from the user.&nbsp;</p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1705785715065" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1705785715065" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1705785715153" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1705785715153" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1705785715185" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1705785715185"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1705785715080" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1705785715080" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="512" height="512" data-width="50%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="512" natural-height="512"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1705785715140" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1705785715140"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="">One of the main factors in adjustability is if the elliptical can adjust to different heights and stride lengths. Especially with the ellipticals that feature seats on our list, this is important to note, so you can get the right fit for you. This becomes increasingly important if multiple people are using the machine, as they will all want to have it fit right for them.</div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1705785715094" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1705785715094" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564763470" data-id="1686564763470"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1705785715077" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1705785715077" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" target="_blank"><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/fc0a1a19-2e31-4fa8-a43b-9c408a123923/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Oleksiy.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="531" height="533" data-width="20%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="531" natural-height="533"></a></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564765807" data-id="1686564765807"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1705785715229" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1705785715229"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" class="" target="_blank">Oleksiy Torokhtiy</a></b></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1705785715173" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1705785715173"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700;">Olympic Weightlifting&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 700; color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Champion</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107341" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673241107341"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">2. Increased Functionality</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107345" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107345" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>With the increased price of these other models often also comes increased functionality. While most of the models on our list feature around <a href="https://www.verywellfit.com/choosing-and-using-resistance-bands-1229709" class="" target="_blank">8 different resistance levels</a>, many higher-end models feature 20-30. On top of the wider range of resistance often comes custom workout programs that are displayed on the screen. These will adjust the resistance automatically for you, creating interval-based resistance training automatically for you. Higher-end machines will also likely have much more accurate tracking of metrics such as speed, and calories burned.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107406" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673241107406"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">3. Price</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107338" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107338" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>While it may go without saying, the biggest difference between cheaper ellipticals and more expensive ones is how much they cost. While the added stability and functionality of more expensive ellipticals are nice, their price point makes them out of reach for most people looking to add an elliptical to their home gym. At the end of the day, the workout you’ll get from a cheaper elliptical versus a more expensive one is virtually the same. For the average person, an elliptical under $300 will serve the purpose it’s meant to fulfill.&nbsp;</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673877030685" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1673877030685" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/856166b1-542f-4724-bcc5-7bf0538d9657/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Female-on-Elliptical.jpg" alt="Using Elliptical by Women" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1024" height="683" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="Using Elliptical by Women" natural-width="1024" natural-height="683"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107333" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107333" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What to Look For in Ellipticals Under $300?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107346" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673241107346" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">1. Adjustability</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107331" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107331" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>One of the main factors in adjustability is if the elliptical can adjust to different heights and stride lengths. Especially with the ellipticals that feature seats on our list, this is important to note, so you can get the right fit for you. This becomes increasingly important if multiple people are using the machine, as they will all want to have it fit right for them.&nbsp;</p><p>Another part of the adjustability of an elliptical is the different resistance levels it can provide during your workout. An elliptical with more resistance levels will give you more variability in your workout. This is especially important if you plan on using your elliptical for <a href="https://www.health.harvard.edu/exercise-and-fitness/interval-training-for-a-stronger-heart" class="" target="_blank">interval training</a>, as more variability in adjustability will give you more options.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107497" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673241107497"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">2. Monitor Functionality</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107356" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107356" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Most ellipticals will come with some form of basic monitor to keep track of your workout. The most common features included in this monitor are the time of your workout, calories burned, speed, and distance covered. Some options that have pulse monitors included will display this information as well. This information must be accurate so that you understand exactly what you’re accomplishing during your workout.</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673876884475" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1673876884475" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/beee96ce-26dd-49af-b91f-eeb87fae9e40/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Performing-Elliptical.jpg" alt="Elliptical in Use" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1024" height="683" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="Elliptical in Use" natural-width="1024" natural-height="683"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107336" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673241107336"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">3. Portability</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107343" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107343" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>While this isn’t a very important factor if you plan on keeping your elliptical in one spot for long periods, portability is useful if you have limited space or plan on moving your elliptical around a lot. While <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stationary_bicycle" class="" target="_blank">most standalone ellipticals</a> are large and difficult to transport, as we’ve covered, there are very compact options available that are incredibly easy to transport or store. While you will be sacrificing some quality when it comes to your workout, these compact models are great for those who want increased portability from their elliptical.&nbsp;</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107514" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673241107514"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">4. Multifunctionality</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107509" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107509" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The most common form of multifunctionality comes from the addition of a seat to an elliptical. This gives the machine the added functionality of being a stationary bike. This is great for those looking for a lower-impact option to incorporate into their workouts, as well as being great for interval training.&nbsp;</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673326486980" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1673326486980" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/7397afeb-0427-44a9-923d-a0f0b8a1f1f8/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Using-Elliptical-by-Women.jpg" alt="Performing Elliptical" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1024" height="683" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="Performing Elliptical" natural-width="1024" natural-height="683"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107507" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673241107507"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">5. Price/Quality&nbsp;</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107521" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107521" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Finally, is the level of quality you’re getting for your money. Unfortunately, there are many low-quality options available that are not worth the money. Luckily, there are plenty of sturdy and solid options available for less than $300. You must do your research to make sure you’re getting a high-quality product for your money.</p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1673241107335" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1673241107335" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1658828961229" data-id="1658828961229"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107334" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107334"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQ</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107519" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107519"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">How Much Should You Spend on an Elliptical?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107522" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107522"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">There is not much reason to spend more than $300 on an elliptical. As we’ve covered, there are plenty of quality options available at this price point. However, if you want increased stability and functionality, you can easily spend thousands of dollars on a machine.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107525" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107525"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Are Ellipticals Worth the Money?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107524" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107524"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Yes, because they provide a great workout right from your home, ellipticals are a great investment. Especially for those who do not want to get a gym membership, ellipticals are a great choice for the money.&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1674663248309" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1674663248309" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context": "https://schema.org","@type": "FAQPage","mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question","name": "Is Doing the Elliptical for 30 Minutes a Day Good?","acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer","text": "Doing elliptical-based exercise for 30 minutes each day has a host of health and fitness benefits including increased cardiovascular fitness, muscular endurance and strength, reduced chances of diseases and illness, and calories burning. It's also in line with the current weekly exercise recommendation of 150 minutes per week."}},{"@type": "Question","name": "Are Ellipticals Better Than Walking?","acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer","text": "Ellipticals provide a low-impact way to exercise, making them more suitable for older populations of people with joint issues. They also burn slightly more calories compared to walking and can be done in any weather and from the comfort of your own home. Which one is better largely depends on personal preference, with a mixture of the two usually being the best choice."}}]}</script></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1673241107332" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1673241107332" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="950" height="534" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/H8bQfRK1wAE" title="When To Use Wrist Wraps In Crossfit" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107523" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107523"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Conclusion</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107526" clas